of George W. Bush]].<ref name="Green Party"/>

Smith premiered two new [[protest_song|protest song]]s in London in September 2006.<ref name="Independent">{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/patti-smith-rails-against-israel-and-us-415231.html |title=Patti Smith Rails Against Israel and US |accessdate=2008-02-08 |author=Jury, Louise |work=[[The_Independent|The Independent]] |publisher=Independent Print Limited |date=2006-09-09 |location=London |archive-date=2012-01-28 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/652AKk8eR?url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/patti-smith-rails-against-israel-and-us-415231.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref> Louise Jury, writing in ''[[The_Independent|The Independent]]'', characterized them as "an emotional indictment of American and Israeli foreign policy". The song "[[Qana|Qana]]"<ref name="#2">[http://www.pattismith.net/audio/qana_band.mp3 "Qana" mp3] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pattismith.net/audio/qana_band.mp3 |date=20080627134616 }} at PattiSmith.net</ref> was about the Israeli airstrike on the Lebanese village of [[Qana|Qana]]. "Without Chains"<ref name="#3">[http://pattismith.net/audio/Without_Chains.mp3 "Without Chains" mp3] {{Wayback|url=http://pattismith.net/audio/Without_Chains.mp3 |date=20080627134616 }} at PattiSmith.net</ref> is about [[Murat_Kurnaz|Murat Kurnaz]], a [[Turkish_people|Turkish]] citizen who was born and raised in Germany, held at [[Guantanamo_Bay_detainment_camp|Guantanamo Bay detainment camp]] for four years. Jury's article quotes Smith as saying:

